⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Prison Chaplain
node ACO · ACO · ⟦The Prison Chaplain:ACO:1f43ac⟧

WHO   — The Prison Chaplain — the voice of the soul
WHAT  — The book's conscience: he argues that forced goodness is no goodness, that a man must be free to choose, even to choose wrong.
WHERE — ACO · A CLOCKWORK ORANGE  Framework inputs: A Clockwork Orange (Anthony Burgess, 1962)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the warning needs its thesis spoken aloud — and it is spoken by a flawed, drinking, doubting priest.
HOW   — By sermons and a lone, futile protest that ‘goodness is something chosen; when a man cannot choose he ceases to be a man.’

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the only one who said it: goodness must be chosen, or it is nothing — strip a man of the choice and you have not saved his soul, you have abolished it.

